<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="66" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,152,294]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,339,229,255]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet composed of the prefix &quot; 
<emphasis box="[870,893,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">bi</emphasis>
-&quot; (two) and Latin &quot; 
<emphasis box="[1120,1187,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">cavus</emphasis>
&quot; (hollow, excavated) refers to the remarkable apical impressions on the elytra.
</paragraph>
